<REFENTRY id="batch">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
batch
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>batch</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
execute commands when the system load permits
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
The specification for <COMMAND>batch</COMMAND> is as specified in the
Single UNIX Specification but with the following differences as listed below.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Files</TITLE>
<PARA>
The files at.allow and at.deny reside in /etc rather than
/usr/lib/cron.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
